    <oval-def:description>Nikolay Ermishkin from the Mail.Ru Security Team and Stewie discovered several vulnerabilities in ImageMagick, a program suite for image manipulation. These vulnerabilities, collectively known as ImageTragick, are the consequence of lack of sanitization of untrusted input. An attacker with control on the image input could, with the privileges of the user running the application, execute code (&lt;a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2016-3714"&gt;CVE-2016-3714&lt;/a&gt;), make HTTP GET or FTP requests (&lt;a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2016-3718"&gt;CVE-2016-3718&lt;/a&gt;), or delete (&lt;a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2016-3715"&gt;CVE-2016-3715&lt;/a&gt;), move (&lt;a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2016-3716"&gt;CVE-2016-3716&lt;/a&gt;), or read (&lt;a href="https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2016-3717"&gt;CVE-2016-3717&lt;/a&gt;) local files.</oval-def:description>
